    <h2>Call Center Salesforce Implementation: Project Overview</h2>
    <div class="app">
        <div class="readyset" id="overview">
            <h3>Mission</h3>
            <dl>
                <dt>What problem does this project address?</dt>
                <dd>
                    Previously the call center used email to manage all their work items. 
                    This is slow and inefficient  and requires constant micromanagement. 
                    This also allows collisions to occur when two agents claim an email.
                </dd>
                <dt>What are the primary of this project?</dt>
                <dd>
                    <ul>
                        <li>To create a call center work management platform that allows rapid onboarding and quick escalation of skill levels for new employees.</li>
                        <li>To create a master data management system that allows managers to easily obtain/find information pertaining to call center work items.</li>
                    </ul>                    
                </dd>
                <dt>What are some key features that define the product?</dt>
                <dd>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Salesforce Platform as a service host</li>
                        <li>Cisco Phone System integration Features:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Click to dial</li>
                                <li>Presence Status integration/sync between salesforce and the Phone System</li>
                                <li>Call Recording Linking to Salesforce Work Items</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>User Interface that is suited to a fast moving call center</li>
                        <li>QFund Loan Management System(LMS) Integration Features:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Opening QFund pages from within Salesforce without login</li>
                                <li>Retrieving pertinent information for the work at hand and display within the salesforce ui</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Custom Chromium Based Browser</li>
                        <li>Skill based routing of work in an evenly distributed manner</li>
                    </ul>
                </dd>
                <dt>What makes this product different from others?</dt>
                <dd>
                    Tight integration of Salesforce with Phone Hardware, a Specific Web Application (QFund) and specific workflows for call center work items pertaining to short term loans.
                </dd>
            </dl>
            <h3>Scope</h3>
            <dl>
                <dt>What is the scope of this project?</dt>
                <dd>
                    Manage All Work items for the call center and provide a method to obtain information about operations.
                </dd>
                <dt>What are the high-level assumptions or ground rules for the project?</dt>
                <dd>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Salesforce is the Extension tool</li>
                        <li>Every Feature added on top of the salesforce ui is optional and graceful degradation must occur in the event the extensions are not there</li>
                    </ul>                    
                </dd>
                <dt>What are we not going to do?</dt>
                <dd>
                    Designate Salesforce as the Database of Record. This is contrary to most salesforce implementations.
                </dd>
            </dl>

            <h3>Status</h3>
            <dl>
